How many copies of this same file are you going to create before there is a better way to specify this?
I was thinking maybe when we get to system10? Just kidding, let me make a common file.
Renaming the file is probably ok, adding Manoj who created the original json in case he has any inputs regarding the file name.

hey @andrew - I think this could break the Tacoma machines ? looking at my commit https://github.com/openbmc/openbmc/commit/df57e3a63ccc7adcf2d8aabe6586295e97a954d9, it seems like we are looking for some pattern in the inventory object to map the ethernet interfaces.

network always creates objects with eth<n> notation. But the inventory manager on our systems seems to create objects inconsistently. In tacoma machines we have only one ethernet interface which comes up with `eth0` in the object path, but in mihawk inventory creates ethernet objects with `ethernet` as leaf node in the object path.And on p10 machines it create ethernet0 & ethernet1 e.t.c

These JSON's basically create the mapping between inventory object to the ethernet interfaces.so that the right mac address can be applied from vpd on to the corresponding ethernet interface during genesis boot.
oh good point, I didn't realize the files were not all the same! Will create a common file for where there is duplication but will utilize the separate files when needed.
